# Backend API Conventions

## Service Landscape

- 21 Python microservices (FastAPI + Pydantic) + 1 Go service (`call-manager` — chi, pgx, redis, websocket)
- Shared Python libraries in `shared/python/`
- Each service has its own `pyproject.toml` with dependencies

## Patterns

- Follow existing service patterns for new endpoints — do not introduce new frameworks
- Consistent error models per service (Pydantic error responses)
- Async handlers by default (Python: `async def`, Go: goroutines)
- Each service owns its own `tests/` directory

## Testing

See `testing-conventions.mdc` for pytest, Vitest, and Playwright conventions.

## Go Service (call-manager)

- Go 1.24+, chi router, pgx for PostgreSQL, gorilla/websocket
- Module at `services/call-manager/go.mod`
